  "prompt": "Where can I buy a Dell PowerEdge R805 server?",
  "response": "The Dell PowerEdge R805 is a high-density 2U server that was popular for its blade-like design and scalability. However, since it's an older model, finding new units directly from Dell might be challenging. Here are several options to consider when looking to purchase a Dell PowerEdge R805 server:\n\n### 1. **Dell Official Channels**\n- **Dell Outlet:** Occasionally, Dell's official outlet may have refurbished or remaining stock of older servers. Check the [Dell Outlet](https://outlet.dell.com/) website regularly.\n- **Dell Partner Network:** Contacting a Dell partner or reseller might help you locate refurbished or pre-owned R805 units.\n\n### 2. **Third-Party Retailers**\n- **Amazon:** Search for \"Dell PowerEdge R805\" on [Amazon](https://www.amazon.com/) to find new, used, or refurbished options from various sellers.\n- **Newegg:** [Newegg](https://www.newegg.com/) sometimes lists older server models through third-party vendors.\n- **CDW:** As a major technology reseller, [CDW](https://www.cdw.com/) might have listings for refurbished PowerEdge R805 servers.\n\n### 3. **Refurbished and Used Server Specialists**\n- **ServerMonkey:** They specialize in refurbished servers and might have the R805 available. Visit [ServerMonkey](https://www.servermonkey.com/).\n- **eBay:** A good platform to find both new old stock and used Dell PowerEdge R805 servers. Check listings on [eBay](https://www.ebay.com/).\n- **IT Resale Stores:** Companies like [TechSoup](https://www.techsoup.org/) or local IT resale shops often have used enterprise hardware.\n\n### 4. **Local and Online Classifieds**\n- **Craigslist:** Depending on your location, you might find local sellers offering the server.\n- **Facebook Marketplace:** Another platform to search for local listings of the Dell PowerEdge R805.\n\n### 5. **Specialized IT Auctions**\n- **Liquid Technology:** Sometimes offers servers through auctions. Visit [Liquid Technology](https://www.liquidtechnology.com/).\n- **GovDeals:** Government surplus auctions can occasionally have enterprise hardware like the R805. Check [GovDeals](https://www.govdeals.com/).\n\n### **Things to Consider:**\n- **Support and Warranty:** Since the R805 is an older model, obtaining warranties might be difficult. Ensure you understand the condition of the server and any available support.\n- **Compatibility:** Verify that the server meets your current technical requirements and is compatible with your existing infrastructure.\n- **Price Comparison:** Prices for older servers can vary widely based on condition (new, refurbished, used) and included accessories. Compare prices across different platforms to ensure you're getting a fair deal.\n\n### **Alternative Options:**\nIf you're unable to find a Dell PowerEdge R805 or if it's not meeting your needs, consider newer Dell PowerEdge models that offer improved performance, energy efficiency, and support. Contacting Dell or a trusted IT consultant can help you find a server that better fits your current requirements.\n\n---\n\n**Useful Links:**\n- [Dell Outlet](https://outlet.dell.com/)\n- [ServerMonkey Dell PowerEdge Servers](https://www.servermonkey.com/category/dell/poweredge-servers)\n- [eBay Dell PowerEdge R805 Listings](https://www.ebay.com/sch/i.html?_nkw=dell+poweredge+r805)\n\nFeel free to reach out if you need further assistance in selecting the right server for your needs!",
